---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	* Central identity and access management cloud service 

	* Controll Access by users, groups, roles

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Tenant

	* A specific instance of AD containing accounts and groups
	* Also called directory
	* Not part of subscription, existed beside subscription
	* For new subscription, a new Tenant creats automatically
	* Can be assigned to multiple subscriptions

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Users and Groups

	* Manages and Stores that are part of Tenant by AD

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

RBAC (Role Based Access Control)

	* Better when we need to provide access at role level
	* Instead of providing it in each user level, to avoid complexicity

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
3 Types of Roles

	1. Owner
	2. Contributer (can't assign roles)
	3. Reader

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Managed Identity

	* Ability to assign AD identity to Azure reources
	* Means, Azure resources can connect to other resources using this identity
	* Means, no need to have credentials
	* 2 Types (System assigned and User assigned)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

OAuth2 

	* Standard protocol for authentication and authorization 
	* Mainly used in Web Apps
	* Here we get access token to access resources

	* JWT Token (Json Web Token)

	* Client App requests Autorization server for token, uses it to access resources

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Azure AD B2C

	* Identity as a Service
	* A Business to Customer service 
	* Works with varouos identity providers
	* Ex: Signin with Apple

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------